# LabWired board map — the single source of truth for which LabWired system
# manifest each Zephyr board target runs against. Shared with the hosted Zephyr
# compiler (labwired-builder). One line per board:
#
#   <qualified Zephyr board target> : <LabWired system manifest filename>
#
# The manifest filename is resolved against the LabWired systems directory
# (--systems-dir, or $LABWIRED_SYSTEMS_DIR, defaulting to <labwired>/configs/systems).
# Add a board by adding one line here. Keep this board-specific: matching only
# on CPU core is not enough because the Zephyr image still touches SoC-specific
# memory-mapped peripherals during boot.

# Model-backed Zephyr target snapshot from Zephyr board.yml SoC metadata.
